cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the problem of automatic tunneling in computer networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a distributed algorithm for path computation, which involves the exchange of messages between nodes, suggesting a possible fit with cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses security issues related to tunneling, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. The algorithmic aspect of the paper, which involves the design and analysis of a new routing protocol, could also make it relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.RO (Robotics).
